< text>
A lot of needless up selling, they broke a part in the car and said they'd do ME a favor by installing the new part for free. Didn't know the part cost 140$. <Rate>5< /Rate>< text>
BOTTOM LINE UP FRONT: Do your research, know what your willing to spend, and don't get upset if they don't want to haggle with you.

I was honestly nervous about buying from Choice after reading many of the reviews here. But, before you move on to another auto dealer, let me shed some light on where (I believe) most of their negative reviews come from.

Andre and his team aren't the most warm and flowery people. And I think that's where customers are usually put off. Customers are used to car salesman being very warm and inviting and complimentary. Andre and his team are curt to the point that they may come off as rude to some people. But honestly, I liked it. I showed them respect, they showed me respect, and nobody had to suck up to anyone else. It was a very mature atmosphere to buy a car, and I appreciated it.

Also, they don't like to haggle, which I can appreciate because they also didn't try to upsell me. They had an amount they were willing to sell at, I had an amount I was willing to buy at, those figures met, and we struck a deal. I asked if they could go lower, they respectfully declined, and that's okay.

Finally, if you're concerned about getting a lemon, do what I did: have a mechanic inspect the car before you finalize your purchase. It was $100, and it gave me full peace-of-mind. Andre was totally okay with my mechanic putting that car to the test.

I couldn't have been happier with my experience at Choice Auto.<//text>

DO NOT SHOP HERE - ILLEGAL, SCAM ARTISTS, FRAUD

I never write reviews online but simply made an account to share my HORRIBLE experience with these SCAM ARTISTS.

2 days ago, I purchased a used Audi from them. Price was 9,998. After reviewing and inputting  exact details offered by Choice Auto into Kelly Blue Book, worth came up around 8,000. After arriving at their lot, we began to haggle with one of the two men at the front. He did not speak very much english and made this interaction difficult, although that is not at all my complaint.

We asked ‚Äú$9,998 is a little high for this car, is it not?‚Äù He turned his computer screen around to us and said what we could only understand as ‚ÄúThis is cheap. My profit is 900. I need to make a profit on this. This or nothing.‚Äù We of course understood, and the Audi being such a wonderful car, we took the deal.

Fast forward after we pay, we‚Äôre driving home and the CHECK ENGINE LIGHT COMES ON. We‚Äôre not too worried, assuming that‚Äôs what we get for purchasing a used car. We already had a scheduled appointment with our trusted mechanic, Ryan GMW (North Aurburn, CA. Definitely give him your business if you have a European car! He‚Äôs great and knows exactly what he‚Äôs talking about!)

By the time we get home (20 miles) and pull into our driveway, the car begins to smell funky. Smoke is coming out from under the hood. We shut the car and back away. We lift the hood but can‚Äôt see what is wrong. We allow the engine 20-30 minutes to cool, then try to finish bringing it up the driveway. Car doesn‚Äôt start.

Car. Does. Not. Start.

He said this car has been illegally smogged and there is not plausible way these people did not know there was something wrong with the car.

I had been looking for a used 4runner for about a month when I found Choice Auto and Truck on craigslist. They had the vehicle I wanted, color and all. My husband and I went to see the truck and the first thing Kevin, the sales man said to us was they just discovered an oil leak on the vehicle and it was scheduled to be fixed the following day. We test drove the vehicle and decided to buy it. Because of their great choices of high quality vehicles my husband also bought a car that day. After having the 4runner for less then a day my check engine light came on. I called Kevin and he said no problem, bring it in and we will take care of it. We took the truck in and problem solved, they changed my O2 sensors and replaced my rear oil seal. A couple days later my starter went out and my check engine light came back on. Again, I called Kevin and told him the problem, he said no problem....bring it in and we will take care of it. I brought my 4runner in again and they replaced my starter and my catalytic converter. To our surprise all these things were replaced no charge to us. My husband and I knew Choice Auto and Truck were under no obligation to fix any of these things by law, but they did. We just drove our 4runner to AZ and it drove beautifully...No problems! Kevin told us over and over again how they go through the vehicles they buy with a fine tooth comb and they stand behind their vehicles and it is true. We are very happy with both of our vehicles. Andrea in financing was great as well. And I believe Wally had a lot to do with making sure our 4runner was fixed. It is likely that we will buy our next vehicles from them! And we have told many of our friends and family about this dealership as well.< /review>

< review>
I have done my research on Toyota 4runners, and I found this lot advertised one of the only list prices under blue-book for a retailer. Curious as to why, I took their very clean '05 4runner down to my mechanic, who found it to be an overall sound vehicle. Unfortunately he discovered a small misfire, which he said could be as simple as a spark plug or an injector, or as serious as bad valves, leading to very expensive repairs down the line. The dealer immediately challenged my integrity and that of my mechanic, and refused to 'fix' anything until I had agreed to buy the vehicle. Obviously that's not a smart move, so I insisted that he fix the problem, then we could make a deal. He wouldn't budge, so bottom line: a potential lemon is sitting on his lot, with his full knowledge, and it's out there just waiting for the naive buyer to come along and be dazzled by his steam cleaning process under the hood. <user_id>108212658778619361777< /user_id><name>Ben Kussmann< /name><Time>1285257251228< /Time><rate>5< /rate><Review>I responded to a Craigslist ad that was placed by this dealership.  They advertised a great price on a 2006 Camry.  I called to confirm the car was still there, and it was.

We visited the dealership and were greeted by Marsha.  She was very calm, and informative.  We test drove two vehicles while we were there, one of which being the Camry.  It seems she would have let us test drive more had we asked.

Marsha mentioned that they do not haggle at their lot, and that they rarely settle for less than the price asked for.  (Again, the price on this car was fantastic, so I could not blame them).  I admired that she stated this before negotiations even began.

I stated we wanted to have lunch be fore we committed to a purchase.  She suggested a nice restaurant that was nearby.  Marsha did not try and pressure us into closing the deal before we left, as most dealerships would.  This showed me she was confident in her asking price, and the quality of the car.

We of course checked out the rest of the dealers on the block after lunch, and found NOTHING that compared in our price range.  We came back to the lot, and purchased the car.

We of course tried to haggle the price anyway. No Dice,  She was not kidding about the no haggle policy.  Though I didn't feel bad about this, because she did mention that up front, and the price was still great.

The cars we looked at were in great condition, and super clean.  Most of this has to due with the previous owner, as it is with most used cars.  The engine compartment was so clean, I would eat off if it (yeah, i'm the type that seriously would).

Overall this was a great experience.  Next car purchase, I will be coming here first.</Review>< Pictures>

< Review>
Dream tobacco is the premier shop for hookah in Anaheim. Family owned they offer a wide selection of tobacco and accessories to meet the needs of the surrounding people. They even carry Tangier products for the heavier hookah smokers out there. They have a ton of different hookah brands and some weird brands also. Everything is priced pretty reasonably and the staff is kind and helpful. If you're ever in the area I would suggest dropping by because they probably have what you're looking for.< /Review>

< Text>
This review is about 1st Nissan service department! Over four years ago I moved to Simi Valley, and have been bringing my Nissan vehicle to 1st Nissan Simi Valley service department every 5,000 to 6,000 miles for routine maintenance, there was one recall issue, and also had a front window washer unit replaced. 1st Nissan became my go-to place for service. BUT NEVER AGAIN WILL I USE THEM. Here is why: Something changed with this service department over the past 6 months. They now seem to operate on a corrupt line of practice as you hear so often of so many other automotive service shops. They make claims of bogus problems that simply do not exist. I am sure they make a lot of up-sells $$$ on people that are na√Øve or simply do not know enough about cars and who fall prey to these tactics, but I have worked on all my cars most of my life from changing my own brakes, plugs and fluids to replacing timing belts to replacing entire engines. 6 Months ago I brought my vehicle in for routine maintenance, oil change, tire rotation and even asked them to change out all my air filters. The price was reasonable and I approved the work. When I came to pick up the vehicle the service agent told me there were two serious issues that needed immediate attention or could create a dangerous situation if left unrepaired. He told me that one of my engine motor mounts was broken, and that my timing belt was making noise and that both needed to be replaced (Total cost for both in excess of $1900). Many customers would probably trust the agent and likely pay for the ‚ÄúNeeded repairs‚Äù and not think twice. I said I would have to think about it before I approved the work (Believe me, if I discovered the vehicle needed those repairs I would have done so). Of course I examined both and found nothing wrong, I even took my vehicle to a friend who is a mechanic and he confirmed that there was absolutely nothing wrong with either. Today 05/16/16 I again took my vehicle in for oil change, tire rotations, and also asked them to clean up the battery which had a little corrosion on the terminals, and (Also asked them to determine why my window washer reservoir was not holding fluid). The agent gave me a quote for all but the fluid reservoir, and I approved. When he called me, he said during their multi-point inspection they determined that my brake lines had ‚ÄúDirty fluid‚Äù and that this would cause adverse pressure on the brake systems and cause faster wear on my pads and that they could replace my brake fluid for only $121. (Sounds very technical and expertise, right? What a line of BS! When I told my friend the mechanic he almost choked with laughter, and said how does an encased hydraulic system get dirty fluid), The service agent also said that while working on my battery that they noticed the ‚Äúvoltage was a little low and that they had another battery in stock and could easily replace it same day" (My battery is just over 1 year old, and works perfectly as the gauge on my console supports). Of course when I picked up my vehicle I asked the tech why during their multi-point inspection didn‚Äôt they notice a broken engine mount or timing belt today like they told me they found 6 months ago when I was last in for service? (I DO WANT TO MENTION THAT MY VEHICLE IS A 2008 WITH ONLY 67,000 MILES) I am explaining each claim with great detail because I want you the reader of this review to be prepared if you hear the same lines from them, maybe it will prevent others from paying for something that they truly do not need, like so many of people do. Please notice I didn‚Äôt mention any of the service personnel‚Äôs names. This is because I do not believe this is the fault of any one employee, but more likely the practice that plagues the entire operations of this business.< /Text>

I could not be happier with my experience at First Nissan in Simi Valley.  I have been researching and shopping for a Murano for about a week and was drawn in to other dealerships with "no haggle" internet sites like TrueCar and Edmunds. These services have become questionable because dealers manipulate other factors once you show up, such as adding hidden fees (a $1500 maintenance fee??), and manipulating interest rates(almost 6% with a 725 credit score--huh?),  so when you show up at the dealership, the bottom line price is not the great deal you think. I drove an hour for one of those deals, and was treated like I was trying to rob the place to get them to honor the deal.  After several terrible experiences, I checked out online reviews and saw that First Nissan in Simi had great customer satisfaction rates, so I emailed them with details of the deal I wanted. Mayra sent me an email and then called me inviting me into meet with the manager. I then got a call from Billy the manager, and was blown away by his friendliness (but not in the sleazy salesman sort of way), honesty and directness.  He offered me a great deal on the phone, and even after he had be hooked, continued looking for Nissan discounts and saved me an extra $10/mth.  Who does that? Other deals would have pocketed it.  I showed up  to the dealership and their were no games or..."oh you wanted car mats with that too?"  I received an extremely fair price and was treated like a valuable customer, all in record time of like 2 hours TOTAL.  That is the way a car sale should go.  Juan was my salesman and he could not have been a nicer, more professional guy.  He completed an orientation with me of the the car and its ridiculous breadth of features. His love and pride of Nissan cars and trucks was evident.  Brian the financial manager was also super friendly as we walked through the paperwork. I never buy dealer add-ons, but actually saw great value in service that repairs tires, replaces windshield, lost keys, and dings.  He probably got me at the right time as I have recently dropped a ton on all of these.  Either way, he was also non-pressure. I really can't say enough good things about this company and its people.  If you are looking for a different, better car-buying experience , call First Nissan.< /review>

< review>
After my first visit, I wrote: "Everyone is very friendly and informative, explaining every step of the process."  At that time, I was told I had a very healthy mouth and teeth.  But on my next visit later that year, I was told I needed major work (tooth extracted and replaced with an implant - a very expensive process).  I was not comfortable with that diagnosis and obtained two "second opinions" from other dentists.  Both the other dentists said an extraction and implant was not necessary.  I got a simple inlay instead and have been very happy with the work done by a different dentist.

Del Dental is fine for simple routine cleanings, etc.  However, if you go there, be wary of possible up-sells and/or unnecessary work.  I would suggest going elsewhere; I have changed to a different dentist and will not be returning to Del Dental.</review>

<Rating>1< /Rating>< Text>
STAY AWAY!

I went here because of all the glowing reviews and got scammed.  I needed a chipped tooth fixed but the dentist decided that one of my crowns needed to be replaced and I was presented with two options, neither of which were covered by my insurance (unknown to me at the time) and ended up paying $650 more than I should have because they used a "name brand" ceramic crown rather than a normal one.

It was a pretty fun conversation to have the receptionist play verbal gymnastics when I asked her directly,  "Does your office have the types of crowns covered by my insurance"  only to have her keep repeating,  "The two options presented to you were not covered by your insurance".

In hindsight, it's obvious this place is a scam; most of the positive reviews are from new accounts and most of the reviews from experienced reviewers are poor.  Stay away.< /Text>

One of the many perks I enjoy as a retiree are my Exchange privileges. The tax-free shopping, the great assortment of products, price matching, and multiple lanes for a quick checkout is a major plus. You're bound to find a great discount if you're a bargain shopper. 20-50% off in some of the clearance sections of clothing and shoe deals. Another plus the MCX just added was the Gap brand! Happy shopping!<//text>
